---
import DocsLayout from '../../layouts/DocsLayout.astro';
import PageHeader from '../../components/PageHeader.astro';
---

<DocsLayout title="Search Trend Scraper" agentDocsSlug="search-trend-scraper">
  <PageHeader
    title="Search Trend Scraper"
    tags={["Naver API", "PostgreSQL", "2-stage ETL"]}
    agentDocsSlug="search-trend-scraper"
  />

  <details>
    <summary>First-Time Setup</summary>
    <div class="details-body">
      <strong>Clone & Install</strong>
      <pre><code>git clone https://github.com/KBWW/search-trend-scraper-async.git
cd search-trend-scraper-async
uv sync</code></pre>
      <strong>Configure Database (.env)</strong>
      <pre><code>cat > .env &lt;&lt; 'EOF'
DATABASE_URL=postgresql://user:pass@host:5432/database
EOF</code></pre>
      <strong>API Credentials</strong> (in <code>scraper.py</code>)
      <ul>
        <li>Naver Datalab API: <code>client_id</code>, <code>client_secret</code></li>
        <li>Naver Keyword Tool API: <code>API_KEY</code>, <code>SECRET_KEY</code>, <code>CUSTOMER_ID</code></li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </details>

  <details>
    <summary>Table Version Manager</summary>
    <div class="details-body">
      <strong>List all versions</strong>
      <pre><code>uv run python -m utils.tbl_version_manager --list
uv run python -m utils.tbl_version_manager -l -t product_search_trend</code></pre>
      <strong>Activate specific version</strong>
      <pre><code>uv run python -m utils.tbl_version_manager --activate product_search_trend 2</code></pre>
      <strong>Cleanup old versions (keep N most recent)</strong>
      <pre><code>uv run python -m utils.tbl_version_manager --cleanup product_raw 3</code></pre>
    </div>
  </details>

  <!-- ── Tabs ──────────────────────────────────────────────── -->
  <div class="tabs">
    <div class="tab-bar" role="tablist">
      <button class="tab-btn active" role="tab" aria-selected="true" data-tab="scraper">1. scraper</button>
      <button class="tab-btn" role="tab" aria-selected="false" data-tab="stmain">2. main</button>
    </div>

    <!-- ── 1. Scraper ──────────────────────────────────────── -->
    <div class="tab-panel active" id="tab-scraper" role="tabpanel">
      <p class="caption">Fetches brand search trends from Naver APIs</p>

      <div class="seg-bar">
        <button class="seg-btn active" data-seg="run" data-group="scraper">Run</button>
        <button class="seg-btn" data-seg="status" data-group="scraper">Status</button>
        <button class="seg-btn" data-seg="config" data-group="scraper">Config</button>
        <button class="seg-btn" data-seg="info" data-group="scraper">Info</button>
      </div>
      <hr />

      <div class="seg-panel active" id="seg-scraper-run">
        <strong>Production Run</strong>
        <pre><code>cd ~/search-trend-scraper-async && \
uv run python scraper.py</code></pre>
      </div>

      <div class="seg-panel" id="seg-scraper-status">
        <strong>Check Output Files</strong>
        <pre><code>ls -la data/$(date +%y%m%d)/</code></pre>
        <strong>View Latest CSV</strong>
        <pre><code>ls data/$(date +%y%m%d)/*_final.csv</code></pre>
      </div>

      <div class="seg-panel" id="seg-scraper-config">
        <strong>APIs Used</strong>
        <table>
          <thead><tr><th>API</th><th>Purpose</th></tr></thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr><td>Naver Datalab</td><td>Search trend ratios (0-100)</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Naver Keyword Tool</td><td>Absolute search volume estimates</td></tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
        <p><strong>Batch Processing:</strong> 5 brands per API call, saves every 100 brands</p>
      </div>

      <div class="seg-panel" id="seg-scraper-info">
        <strong>What it does</strong>
        <ol>
          <li>Loads brand list from active <code>brand</code> table</li>
          <li>For each batch of 5 brands:
            <ul>
              <li>Fetches search trends from Naver Datalab API</li>
              <li>Fetches keyword volumes from Naver Keyword Tool API</li>
              <li>Estimates absolute search counts</li>
            </ul>
          </li>
          <li>Saves intermediate results every 100 brands</li>
          <li>Outputs final CSV to <code>data/YYMMDD/</code></li>
        </ol>
        <strong>Output CSV Columns</strong>
        <table>
          <thead><tr><th>Column</th><th>Description</th></tr></thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr><td>period</td><td>Week start date</td></tr>
            <tr><td>ratio</td><td>Relative search ratio (0-100)</td></tr>
            <tr><td>title</td><td>Brand name</td></tr>
            <tr><td>abs_count</td><td>Estimated absolute search count</td></tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- ── 2. Main ─────────────────────────────────────────── -->
    <div class="tab-panel" id="tab-stmain" role="tabpanel">
      <p class="caption">Processes scraped data into proportional search metrics</p>

      <div class="seg-bar">
        <button class="seg-btn active" data-seg="run" data-group="stmain">Run</button>
        <button class="seg-btn" data-seg="status" data-group="stmain">Status</button>
        <button class="seg-btn" data-seg="config" data-group="stmain">Config</button>
        <button class="seg-btn" data-seg="info" data-group="stmain">Info</button>
      </div>
      <hr />

      <div class="seg-panel active" id="seg-stmain-run">
        <strong>Production Run</strong>
        <pre><code>cd ~/search-trend-scraper-async && \
uv run python main.py --target 260203</code></pre>
        <strong>Short Flag</strong>
        <pre><code>cd ~/search-trend-scraper-async && \
uv run python main.py -t 260203</code></pre>
      </div>

      <div class="seg-panel" id="seg-stmain-status">
        <strong>Check New Table Version</strong>
        <pre><code>uv run python -m utils.tbl_version_manager -l -t product_search_trend</code></pre>
        <strong>Query Output Table (SQL)</strong>
        <pre><code>SELECT group_id, period, search_trend
FROM product_search_trend_002
LIMIT 10;</code></pre>
      </div>

      <div class="seg-panel" id="seg-stmain-config">
        <table>
          <thead><tr><th>Argument</th><th>Description</th></tr></thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr><td>--target, -t</td><td>Date folder to process (YYMMDD)</td></tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
        <strong>Input Tables (auto-detected active versions)</strong>
        <table>
          <thead><tr><th>Table</th><th>Purpose</th></tr></thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr><td>product_review</td><td>Weekly review counts per group</td></tr>
            <tr><td>product_raw</td><td>Product-to-brand mappings</td></tr>
            <tr><td>brand</td><td>Brand reference data</td></tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>

      <div class="seg-panel" id="seg-stmain-info">
        <strong>What it does</strong>
        <ol>
          <li>Loads <code>*_final.csv</code> from target directory</li>
          <li>Gets active table versions for <code>product_review</code>, <code>product_raw</code>, <code>brand</code></li>
          <li>For each brand:
            <ul>
              <li>Aligns dates to weekly periods (Monday-based)</li>
              <li>Calculates review proportion per group per week</li>
              <li>Merges with brand trend data</li>
            </ul>
          </li>
          <li>Creates versioned output table (e.g., <code>product_search_trend_002</code>)</li>
        </ol>
        <strong>Formula</strong>
        <pre><code>search_trend = abs_count × (group_reviews / total_brand_reviews)</code></pre>
        <strong>Output Table Schema</strong>
        <table>
          <thead><tr><th>Column</th><th>Type</th><th>Description</th></tr></thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr><td>group_id</td><td>VARCHAR(50)</td><td>Product group identifier</td></tr>
            <tr><td>period</td><td>TIMESTAMP</td><td>Week start date</td></tr>
            <tr><td>search_trend</td><td>FLOAT</td><td>Proportional search count</td></tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</DocsLayout>
